ive metrics analysis, while directly implicating `Redis` isn't possible without its metric in the list, the indirect impact of Redis on cartservice based on increased `rrt_max` is plausible.\n- Metrics indicate major service-level impacts, especially `CartService` and `CurrencyService-2`.\n\n### JSON Output\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"rrt_max\", \"rrt\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"Redis\",\n      \"reason\": \"Trace evidence has shown significant impact by direct correlation with CartService delay, metrics indicate service level impact of increased `rrt_max` not sufficiently explained by other specific components.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"CartService latency is significantly elevated, may be influenced by database IO spikes; yet Redis traces align with observed CartService delays.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```"}
